"""
Aleph skill CLI — search and read documents, emails, and entities on an
OCCRP Aleph instance, plus an encrypted-sparseimage vault that holds the
API credentials and any research products you produce alongside.

Two command groups:

  aleph search|read|expand|browse|tree|similar|hubs|sources [args]
                          # Aleph API tools — see SKILL.md
  aleph vault <subcmd>    # vault management — init/unlock/lock/status/env/
                          # mountpoint/exec/set/get/list

Configuration is via environment, with auto-discovery from the local vault
when this script is run from a project directory containing a mounted
.vault.sparseimage:

  ALEPH_URL=https://aleph.occrp.org   # falls back to vault secrets.json
  ALEPH_API_KEY=<your-key>             # falls back to vault secrets.json
  ALEPH_SESSION=<name>                 # default: "default"; logical label for
                                       # research products (notes, reports)
  ALEPH_SESSION_DIR=<path>             # default: <vault>/research, else ~/.aleph
  ALEPH_DB_PATH=<path>                 # override SQLite location; default is
                                       # $ALEPH_SESSION_DIR/aleph.sqlite

State (aliases, response cache, entity blobs) lives in
  $ALEPH_SESSION_DIR/aleph.sqlite       # shared across sessions on this vault
"""

